ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:name: Urgent Care Centre: St Thomas Hospital, Lambeth, London
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:address: St Thomas Hospital, Westminster Bridge Road, London, SE1 7EH
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:referralText: You can go straight to this service. You do not need to telephone beforehand.
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:notes: Referral Information: REFERRAL METHOD Patient to self-present at A&E reception. ITK not seen by person on reception. FURTHER INFO GP and Emergency Nurse Practitioner led Urgent Care Centre (UCC) located within the Emergency Department (ED). Patients should first register at ED reception at St Thomas Hospital and will then be directed the short distance to UCC. The UCC will endeavour to see all patients ASAP, but patients are generally seen in order of arrival. Blood tests - 7.30am-6pm, Monday to Friday (last patient entry at 5.45pm)

ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:name: Urgent Treatment Centre: University College London Hospital, Camden, London
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:address: University College Hospital, 235 Euston Road, London, NW1 2BU
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:referralText: You can go straight to this service. You do not need to telephone beforehand.
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:notes: Referral Information: OVERVIEW Urgent treatment centre - PLEASE ADVISE PATIENTS THAT THEY SHOULD ATTEND EMERGENCY DEPARTMENT. REFERRAL CRITERIA NHS 111 - No patient information will be sent through, please DO NOT advise patients that the UTC will be expecting them. Patients MUST present in person at the Emergency Department reception. This is part of the Emergency Department at UCLH not a stand-alone service. EXCLUSIONS Emergency Department will assess X-ray is provided only for patients referred from Urgent Care Center. FURTHER INFORMATION Service provides X-Ray 24 HRS The UTC will NOT provide any advice over the telephone.

ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:referralText: You can go straight to this service. You do not need to telephone beforehand.
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:notes: Referral Information: OVERVIEW Urgent Care Centre REFERRAL CRITERIA Please advise patient to attend. The patient’s information will be sent across to Whittington UCC - IMPORTANT: THIS IS BACK-UP INFORMATION ONLY, the patient will still be triaged on arrival as normal and will NOT have an appointment booked. Service accepts referrals from London Ambulance Services. EXCLUSIONS None. FURTHER INFORMATION X-Ray opens 24 HRS For more information please contact service directly.

ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:name: Walk-in Centre: Angel Medical Practice WIC, Islington, London
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:address: Ritchie Street Health Centre, 34 Ritchie Street, London, N1 0DG
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:referralText: You can go straight to this service. You do not need to telephone beforehand.
ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:notes: Referral Information: OVERVIEW: Public telephone number is working until 18.30. After please call Non- public telephone number to check availability. After 12:00pm, if patients calling NHS 111 need to see a GP within a certain timeframe, please advise them to go back to their registered GP or to another walk-in service. Open to unregistered patients and patients who cannot access their own GP practice. NOTE: Patients information will be sent electronically to this service. However it is a Walk-in service only, so advise patients 111 cannot book them an appointment. This service uses information sent across for monitoring purposes only. REFERRAL CRITERIA: Patients must attend in person and CANNOT phone in advance to access this service. On arrival, they will be allocated a timed appointment slot. Occasionally patients will be directed elsewhere if there are no appointments left in the service for that day. Open until 8pm, but appointments are all allocated by 2.30pm. EXCLUSIONS: What we are UNABLE to help with: • Long term health problems and chronic illnesses • Referrals & investigations for further care • Medication reviews/Test results/Sick notes • Repeat Prescriptions without evidence of the medication • Serious medical & road traffic emergencies • Severe allergic reactions • Wounds that require suturing • Accidental or deliberate overdose of drugs • Long term wound dressings • Dental problems • Emergency follow-up care FURTHER INFORMATION: Ritchie Street Group Practice does NOT accept phone calls on behalf of the service.

ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:name: Integrated Urgent Care CAS: LAS Speak To and Contact, Tower Hamlets, London

ns1:serviceType.ns1:name: Integrated Urgent Care (IUC) Clinical Assessment Service (CAS)

ns1:ServiceCareSummaryDestination.ns1:notes: Referral Information: Service Overview LAS provide the Integrated Urgent Care (IUC) service for North East London. The service covers the London boroughs of Barking and Dagenham, Havering, Redbridge, Newham, City and Hackney, Tower Hamlets and Waltham Forest. The clinical hub is virtual and patients will be triaged by an appropriate clinician such a GP, Paramedic, Nurse or Pharmacist. REFERRAL CRITERIA: Service is available to patients residing in, registered with a GP in, or located within the London boroughs of Barking and Dagenham, Havering, Redbridge, Newham, City and Hackney, Tower Hamlets and Waltham Forest. Please advise the patient that they will get a call back within the disposition timeframe. If the caller does not get a call back, please ask them to redial 111. EXCLUSIONS: Patients NOT residing in, registered with a GP in, or located within the London boroughs of Barking and Dagenham, Havering, Redbridge, Newham, City and Hackney, Tower Hamlets and Waltham Forest. FURTHER INFORMATION: If there is an operational problem, 111/IUC staff can contact the LAS Supervisor Line on 0207 783 6953
